The paper discusses the verification of cryptographic protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of pushdown automata suggests a focus on formal language theory and automata theory (cs.LO), and the use of programming language means suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the interpretive approach used in the experiment, which suggests a focus on formal methods and semantics (cs.FL). Finally, the paper describes the termination guarantees of the verification process, which suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
